<br>
However, just a few random ideas:<br>
<br>
Make Wizards the Masters of Space, Time, and Damage.<br>
<br>
New spell lines: <br>
<br>
Timestop - Mob is mezzed and immune to all damage and spells other than Cancel Magic (which stops the Timestop).  Single target only, high recast (15 seconds) but guaranteed duration (15 seconds).  In situations where adds are common an enchanter is still better, and the wizard would be better off nuking. Overwritten by Enchanter and Bard mez<br>
<br>
Timeheal - Increases the amount of mana and hipoints given per tick in increments of 1/6th (depending on level and type of spell).  Does not apply to 'CC' spells or Lich Form.<br>
<br>
Time Dilation - Increases the cast time of all spells on the target.  Does not effect proc spells.  <br>
<br>
Time Haste - Group Spell Buff - Decreases the cast time of all spells except % heals.  Relatively short duration.  Does not effect Detrimental AE spells<br>
<br>
Paradox - Instant Intra-Zone Evac, removes all effects and leaves all characters OOM.  In the Lore the cast time should be longer, but you're just moving that damn fast.<br>
<br>
Of course, they should have more interesting names than that, such as <br>
G'ravv's Lesser/Minor/normal/Major Time Heal <br>
Lorend's Lesser/Minor/normal/Major Time Dilation <br>
Ainstyne's Paradox <br>
Starfyre's Lesser/Minor/normal/Major Time Cessation <br>
Ognit's Lesser/Minor/normal/Major Casting Expediation  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarnin>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Likes to wear<BR>Yoda Under-Roos</span><br>  Posts: 2514<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/4/02 2:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~~</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Timestop - Mob is mezzed and immune to all damage and spells<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
