<br>
Sure, under certain circumstances, you're absolutely right. But those are very specific circumstances, and don't relate to our inability to be welcome in most group configurations.<br>
<br>
Sure, sometimes we rock in groups. But most the time we aren't up to par, not because we don't deal good damage, but because it's not noticed by our peers. Other classes know what we offer them, and they really don't care.<br>
<br>
I'm trying to have you guys come up with a solution, and giving us more damage and better mana efficiency isn't it. SOE will never go for it. They also won't go for improving our AoE spells because like I said, they're scared shitless that we'll actually use them.<br>
