Also, Jarnin, rethink your rules.  No damage increases, No efficiency increases, no buffs, no crowd control,   There are only 3 things that matter in Groups:<br>
1) 1 mob at a time translates into crowd control, soemthing wizards are already somewhat good at if they know what they are doing, but nowhere near as good as a Monk, ShadowKnight, Bard, or Enchanter.<br>
2) Mana Regen:  Mana Pool is irrelevent, if you expend more mana per mob than you can regen in that time, it is useless.<br>
3) DPS: Mob HP - Your DPS + any regen and heals &gt; Your HP - Mobs DPS +Your Regen.  Want to discuss range?  Kiting essentially negates the Mob's DPS, thats why we can do it.  Slows are the best DPS buff you can have.<br>
<br>
Now, who are the masters of thes?<br>
CC: Monks, Enchanters, Bards, ShadowKnights<br>
Mana Regen: Clerics &amp; Druids (effiecient Heals), Enchanters, Bards<br>
DPS: Clerics(heals), Warriors(HP), Rogues(constant damage), Enchanters(Haste &amp; Slows), Shaman(Slows &amp; Haste)<br>
<br>
There is nothing else.  If you look at it, you can actually work out a larger grand unified formula. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=infotainmentx>Infotainmentx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/4/02 11:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~~</span><hr size=1> I've always wondered why Mages, who have so much utility, got the DS line over Wizards who have very little.<br>
