My feeling right now is that the Plane of Knowledge has almost totally killed the usefulness of wizard teleports.  I find that I rarely need the normal ports anymore.  When I was making my original character, the ability to teleport myself weighed very heavily in my choice of class.  While I ended up choosing Magician, anyway, the point is that ports were a major consideration for me.  Now?  They wouldn't be a consideration at all.   <br>
<br>
On the other hand, it seems like I've evacced a lot more since PoP.  Often, returning to camps from the zone-in is trivial, and it's better to evac and run right back to your camp at full power than deal with downtime from rez effects.  How evacs will work out in higher level zones I don't know.<br>
<br>
Personally, I love the access I have to the portals as a high level raider.  The ability to get myself around basically just takes some of the burden off the Wizards and Druids in the guild.  I really think the lower level game has lost something though, because of this.  What is the point of running across Antonica ever again?  Now it's Freeport or Qeynos, with a few possible XP zones in between.<br>
<br>
