<br>
The rules:<br>
1. No Buffs (I am assuming targetted Buffs and not self Buffs)<br>
2. No Pets<br>
3. No changes to our nuking ability<br>
4. No changes to our current AoE spells<br>
5. Our new ability can't allow us to raid better<br>
6. Our new ability can't allow us to solo better<br>
<br>
A self-only buff. Duration, maybe 30 seconds to one minute.  Effect would be: 1) a % aggro reduction on subsequent spell casts for duration.  2) An AE 'pulsed' effect (like how bard songs break .. err.. work) that imparts a 'small but useful' melee effect for the duration (a DS, Haste component, improved chance to critical, magic damage bonus of a point or two,  etc.).<br>
<br>
Sort of breaks Rule 1, but its a self buff and we have those already.  I am sort of partial to self-only buffs as they allow me to keep my desired target yet apply a spell to myself.  Rule 2 is not broken.  It bends Rule 3 a bit, as an aggro redution does alter our 'ability to nuke' but does not alter any nukes.  Rule 4 may be at issue as a % aggro reduction may allow rains to be cast sooner, however, would likely void effect 2 as you wouldn't be close enough to the melee peeps to get the effect.  Rule 5 would is also at issue for similar reasons as Rule 4, but add to that the numerous Boss AE spells and short duration may counter that.  Rule 6 is a non-issue as reduce aggro while soloing is pointless and most things that are solo'd post level 10 (guessing. Its been a while) will kill you very quickly if your trying to swing a stick at it.<br>
<br>
<br>
I posted in another thread much to the degree that Jarnin has stated here, that other classes can't 'see' what we bring to a group.  With the exception of crits, our damage is hidden behind a descriptive sentence and a 'poof' of sparkels which many people probably have turned off, moved to window so they don't have to see it, or goes unnoticed.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Also posted in another thread is the idea of group bonuses based on class composition of the group.  While general to all classes, is still a good idea to bring up.<br>
