<br>
If you're in a /raid group, you are &quot;normal.&quot;<br>
If you're solo, you are &quot;normal.&quot;<br>
If you're in a standard 6-person group, you get<br>
a bonus. <br>
<br>
Possible Bonuses: <br>
<br>
* &quot;x&quot;% damage bump on ALL damage spells.  Maybe it scales to +5% / group member so a 6 person group nets you +30% damage.  Maybe base it off of the number of wizards in the group.<br>
<br>
* &quot;x&quot;% mana reduction.  All of YOUR spells cost less to cast.  Increases our DPS in groups by giving us more nuking power ONLY in a group.<br>
<br>
* As the masters of damage, we know how to mitigate it.  As a proc'd effect, all people in a radius that would take melee damage are simply missed.  This is borderline a group buff, but there's no buff icon so I threw it in. =P<br>
Maybe may 1 in 10 attacks miss or something.  Maybe 1 in 20.  *shrug*<br>
<br>
*  Another borderline group buff, but we act as a focus for the rest of the groups spells, increasing all spells by 5% per wizard in the group.  Cleric + 5 wizards = +25% healing.  Wizards get +25% nuking power/mana reduction.<br>
<br>
Groups are already chainpulling with zero downtime so our nuking would simply replace the damage of , say, a thief/monk and could be balanced against that.<br>
<br>
This gives us better rains, better DD, better spells  as long as we're grouped and not any other time.<br>
