<br>
why is it that enchanters are the only class that get a viable means of crowd control in most any situation, bards etc. dont cut it most of the time. Yes, clerics are the most viable healers, but in many many grouping situations, a shammy, or even a druid is just as viable. But almost nowhere is a non enchanter crowd controler reliable enought or efficient enought to hack it. Why can't they step up and give another class, a less effective, but still reliable form of crowd control. And possibly could that class be the wizard class, and if so, what type of crowd control line would suit our style?:P Anybody have thoughts on this? I know im out on a limb, but its an interesting train of thought.<br>
<br>
I also liked the idea that was posted about giving people a DS that hurts the mob ever time they hit the mob, that is a good idea, maybe make a fire line, and ice line, and a magic line, perhaps magic based one that has a chance to stun ( only and interrupt 0 second stun of course) and some group and AE ones at the high end, i think by increasing the dps of the melee in the group we would be very VERY desirrable, AND the BEST part is it does NOT effect our soloing in ANY way. i like this idea immensly))<br>
<br>
oh and also, make the DS( or DE; Damage Enhancer, as i have decided to coigne it:P) cost us mana out our arse so it is not viable to buff a whole raid or even a whole group, perhaps put a long recast on it so we have to use it like chanters use boon, only on MA, and MAYBE one other.<br>
